purpose: The commit fixes a potential use-after-free bug by preventing command queuing when HCI_UNREGISTER is set.
The commit removes an unnecessary include of asm/termios.h in n_hdlc.c since linux/tty.h already includes termios.h. This is a code cleanup to simplify header dependencies.
The commit updates the documentation for a 'N/A' metric in store operations, reflecting changes in the report table.
The commit fixes issues with vma lock handling during split and unmapping, addressing race conditions and ensuring proper lock management to prevent future bugs.
The commit adds documentation for AVDD and MICVDD power supplies in the device tree bindings for the Realtek rt5682s codec.
The commit fixes a resource leak by adding an iounmap() call in the remove function to properly free resources that were not being released.
Removal of an unused 'work' field from struct mlx5e_async_ctx to clean up the code.
The commit changes the data type of cfg80211_auth_request::key_idx from unsigned (u8) to signed (s8) to avoid static analysis warnings when -1 is assigned.
The commit sorts CONFIG_SURFACE_PLATFORMS in RISC-V defconfig files, removing commented-out lines without changing functionality.
The commit refactors the code by replacing direct checks with a helper function to determine FD mode.
The commit modifies self-tests to skip RTC-related tests when the RTC is not present, preventing unnecessary test failures.
The commit removes a redundant assignment to the variable 'bytes' which was not used elsewhere in the code, improving code clarity.

The commit decouples rcuscale from RCU Tasks, allowing rcuscale to function without requiring RCU Tasks. This involves modifying configuration files and code to conditionally include RCU Tasks only when necessary.
The commit removes a duplicated phrase 'be split' in a comment within the spte.h file, improving code readability.
The commit reverts a change in how clock tables are populated to fix a bug causing underflow issues.
The commit adds a compatible string for the Renesas RZ/V2L SoC's Mali-G31 GPU to device tree bindings.
The commit renames the struct pcie_port to dw_pcie_rp across multiple files in the DW PCIe core driver to improve naming consistency.
The commit fixes a clang -Wformat warning by correcting the format specifier in a debug message to match the argument's promoted type.
The commit fixes a bug in the branch range check for MIPS jump labels by correctly casting the upper bound to long, ensuring proper signed comparison and preventing warnings.
The commit removes a HW_VAR case from SetHwReg8188EU() by directly calling the function, simplifying code as part of removing an unwanted HAL layer.
The commit changes a global symbol to static in the arm64 CPU errata handling code to address a sparse warning.
The commit corrects the device tree bindings by removing incorrect interrupt flags, ensuring proper configuration and preventing potential bugs.
The commit refactors array allocation in struct ctrl_ref by renaming variables and functions from 'dyn' to 'array', improving code clarity without changing functionality.
The commit adds support for additional PMICs and SoCs by updating the socinfo driver with new model identifiers.
The commit updates the handling of chip cuts in the rtl8xxxu driver to recognize all possible versions from A (0) to P (15), improving logging accuracy.
The commit removes the custom .is_enabled state from PRCMU clocks since the core already handles it, simplifying the code.
The commit restructures and reduces the use of #ifdef CONFIG_XIP_KERNEL in the RISC-V memory management initialization code, improving code readability and maintainability.
The commit enables QUP and GPI DMA hardware in the device tree to support future I2C functionality.
The commit improves code comments, corrects a typo, and adjusts coding style for better readability.
The commit fixes an infinite loop that occurs when failing to acquire the HW semaphore during resource release. It replaces the loop with error logging and exit.
The commit updates the pcm3168a driver to use modern ASoC DAI terminology by replacing 'master_mode' with 'provider_mode', improving code clarity and aligning with current standards.
The commit removes unnecessary conditional compilation directives and comments related to IS_SWAPFILE, which was always defined.
The commit adds functionality to handle GTP echo requests and responses, ensuring compliance with specifications by implementing necessary message handling.

The commit replaces several instances of cpumask_next_* functions with their cpumask_first_* equivalents where appropriate, improving code efficiency and correctness. It also introduces a new function, cpumask_first_zero(), to find the first unset CPU in a cpumask.
The commit removes a call to 'dtim_assoc' IOVAR which was causing console errors during roaming due to unsupported firmware functionality.
The commit adds support for a platform configuration without an amplifier by introducing new device IDs and ACPI matches.
The commit adds a check to fail zero-copy sendmsg requests when the socket does not support it, thus preventing potential bugs and improving reliability.

The commit modifies the LaTeX preamble to conditionally load xeCJK.sty only if both Noto Sans CJK SC font and xeCJK.sty are present. This addresses issues on certain distributions where missing dependencies caused build errors.
The commit modifies the checkpatch script to allow macros starting with 'case', preventing false errors where these macros are commonly used.
The commit refactors the simpledrm driver to use atomic helpers instead of simple-KMS helpers, improving code structure and maintainability without introducing functional changes.

The commit adds a new JPEG decode worker interface to support parallel execution of three hardware decoders on MT8195. It includes new functions for managing hardware states and parameters, along with necessary struct updates.
The commit removes unnecessary VPRINTK() calls and the ata_scsi_dump_cdb() function, as their functionality is redundant with existing tracepoints.

The commit adds support for entering a low-power state (zstate) during extended vblank periods when using Freesync. It modifies several files to check conditions for zstate entry, calculate optimized timings, and update hardware registers accordingly.
The commit fixes a CFI failure by correcting the function parameter type from uint32_t to enum kfd_preempt_type in hqd_destroy(). This addresses a specific bug causing system failures.
The commit corrects the 'resets' property name in a device tree binding file and adds 'additionalProperties: false' to enforce schema strictness.
The commit adds a compiler flag to suppress an array-bounds warning in GCC 12 for the ath9k driver, improving code maintainability by reducing warnings.
The commit replaces pm_runtime_get_sync with pm_runtime_resume_and_get to simplify code in the sun8i-ss-prng.c file.

The commit refactors the io_uring subsystem by moving fixed file installation and removal functions to the appropriate location within the codebase. It modifies function parameters to use the ring context (ctx) instead of the request (req), improving code organization and maintainability.
The commit updates device tree bindings to split G1 and G2 decoder blocks into separate nodes with individual configurations.
The commit removes a redundant macro and combines it into another to simplify the code structure.
